~ initialize_local_variables
do Variables.add_local("know", false)
do Variables.add_local("cult", false)
do Variables.add_local("questions", 0)
do Variables.add_local("wait", false)
do Variables.add_local("unaffected", false)
do Variables.add_local("gift", false)
do Variables.add_local("elders", false)
do Variables.add_local("sacrifice", false)
=> start

~ start
You wake up feeling dizzy. You get out of bed and make your way to the main room. Once there, you take your place behind the work station. You look around for a bit before you start hearing heavy footsteps coming down the stairs.
Shopkeeper: Morning, there. I see you're itching to get started. Sleep well?
- Morning. Slept just fine. 
	Shopkeeper: Good. Wouldn't want you tired on your first day. Especially after such a long journey.[do Variables.set_var("know", true)]
	- How do you know so much about me already?
		Shopkeeper: Your arrival was heralded by the Elders.
		Shopkeeper: They told of someone bearing the Gift who would soon come help me around with the shop. Goddess knows I could use it. 
		Shopkeeper: To be completely honest, though, you never know with them. Their predictions have been wrong just as often as they've been right. 
		Shopkeeper: ...Make sure not to tell anyone I said that. 
		Shopkeeper: I've got my own connection with the Goddess, though. She told me what I needed to know Herself.
		- I see. 
			Shopkeeper: So, got any other questions for me before we get to work?
			- None. 
				Shopkeeper: Okay then. Let's get started. => tutorial 
			- Still have a few, actually.
				Shopkeeper: Shoot. => questions 
