~ questions
Shopkeeper: ... 
- Were you waiting for me last night? Didn't even get to properly knock before you opened the door. [if Variables.get_var("wait") == false]
	Shopkeeper: Oh, well, uh, kind of. I'm sorry if that was weird. [do Variables.mod_var("questions", 1)][do Variables.set_var("wait", true)]
	Shopkeeper: It's just that I've known for a while someone bearing the Gift would come, and yesterday I felt this urge to look out the window right before you came into view.
	Shopkeeper: And there you were. As soon as I saw you, I somehow knew it was you. Can't explain it more than that, though I wish I could.
	Shopkeeper: Plus, I didn't want your knocking to wake Sarah up, truth be told. She's a light sleeper. 
	- To be honest, I, myself, kind of knew this was your house even before Joan pointed it to me.
		Shopkeeper: There you have it. => questions 
	- Err, not sure how I feel about that. 
		Shopkeeper: I know I'm being odd again. But it's the truth. => questions
